result.formatted_address: Keswick Court, 3 Keswick St, Causeway Bay, Hong Kong
result.name: Nam Loong Cafe

reviews.text:
I highly recommend this to local & tourists.
Nice traditional Hong Kong food: Egg tart, lemon tea, fries, noodles, rice, fish/ pork burger.
All are good, come here to have lunch or tea. They have tea set at 2:30.
The build is also very traditional & nice.
And there is something very special:
Since there are 2 floors & the kitchen is upstairs, they got a very old & special “Meal lift” working.
This is very special & unique, i think there are only a very few restaurants using this equipment.
Best egg tart ever. Bought mine in the morning when it was still warm *drool*
worst service I have ever had. I tried this restaurant many times but got yelled every single time, and staffs would keep nagging the customers.
Very reasonable prices. Traditional Hong Kong style lunch meals aka comfort food. Good size portion. Many Hong Kong regulars eat here.
Lunch place. Usually not crowded.

reviews.text: 焗豬扒意粉好ok👍👍
多士及麵包類食物好吃
懷舊裝修，新派食品，有特式！
每次到利園附近工作，都必定會到南龍食晏或下午茶，因為出品穩定又夠份量，最緊要係杯咖啡飲得！至於服務就比一般茶餐廳…好少少！
